description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a senior experienced, dynamic, high performing midwife to join the senior midwifery management team as a Matron for Maternity Services at Ipswich Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a clinically credible midwife with a broad range of midwifery experience and exceptional clinical ability. We need someone who possesses strong clinical leadership and who has excellent communication and networking skills. We are currently in the process of rolling out 100% continuity of carer and therefore need someone who is able to support the maternity team through a period of transformation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be self -motivated, enthusiastic and have a distinct passion for maternity services with a drive for continuous improvement in maternity safety and experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have responsibility for the inpatients areas including labour ward, antenatal and postnatal ward, triage and the Birth Centre,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role is a challenging one, but one that you will be supported in and your personal and professional growth will be encouraged and developed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a five day a week post, with on call commitment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this role is subject to a DBS check which will be charged to the successful candidate. Full details can be found within the ‘DBS Information’ documents attached to this advert.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlison LittlerJob titleHead of MidwiferyEmail addressalison.littler@esneft.nhs.ukTelephone number01473 703005Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion or visit to the unit please contact Alison Littler&lt;/p&gt;
